# Data Access & Mutation Patterns

## Query helpers — `db/queries/` is the only place for DB calls

All Drizzle queries (selects, inserts, updates, deletes) must live in dedicated helper files under `db/queries/`. **Never** write a raw Drizzle query inline inside a Server Component, Server Action, or anywhere else in the app. Always call a helper from `db/queries/`.

### File layout

```
db/
  schema.ts
  index.ts
  queries/
    decks.ts   ← all deck reads & writes
    cards.ts   ← all card reads & writes
```

### Writing a query helper

Query helpers are plain async functions that accept typed arguments. They own the Drizzle query and nothing else — no auth, no Zod, no redirects.

```typescript
// db/queries/decks.ts
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";
import { and, eq } from "drizzle-orm";

export async function getDecksByUser(userId: string) {
  return db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
}

export async function getDeckByIdAndUser(deckId: number, userId: string) {
  const [deck] = await db
    .select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));
  return deck ?? null;
}

export async function createDeckRecord(userId: string, name: string, description?: string) {
  const [deck] = await db
    .insert(decks)
    .values({ clerkUserId: userId, name, description })
    .returning();
  return deck;
}

export async function updateDeckRecord(deckId: number, userId: string, data: { name?: string; description?: string }) {
  await db
    .update(decks)
    .set(data)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));
}

export async function deleteDeckRecord(deckId: number, userId: string) {
  await db
    .delete(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));
}
```

## Data Retrieval — Server Components only

Never fetch data inside Client Components or Route Handlers for page-level reads. Call a `db/queries/` helper directly from the Server Component.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Server Component calls a query helper
import { getDecksByUser } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/");
  const decks = await getDecksByUser(userId);
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle query in a Server Component
export default async function DecksPage() {
  const decks = await db.select().from(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.clerkUserId, userId));
}

// ❌ BAD — fetching inside a Client Component
"use client";
export function DeckList() {
  const [decks, setDecks] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => { fetch("/api/decks").then(...) }, []);
}
```

## Mutations — Server Actions only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must use Server Actions (`"use server"`). Never use Route Handlers for mutations triggered from the UI. The Server Action handles auth + Zod validation, then delegates the DB work to a `db/queries/` helper.

## Input Validation — Zod required, no FormData

Every Server Action must:
1. Accept a typed TypeScript argument (never `FormData`).
2. Parse and validate that argument with a Zod schema before touching the database.
3. Call a `db/queries/` helper — never write a raw Drizzle query inside the action.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — action validates, then calls a query helper
"use server";
import { z } from "zod";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { createDeckRecord } from "@/db/queries/decks";

const CreateDeckSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof CreateDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = CreateDeckSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error("Invalid input");
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
  return createDeckRecord(userId, parsed.data.name, parsed.data.description);
}

// ❌ BAD — raw Drizzle query inside the action
export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  await db.insert(decks).values({ clerkUserId: userId, ...parsed.data });
}

// ❌ BAD — raw FormData, no Zod validation
export async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const name = formData.get("name") as string;
  await db.insert(decks).values({ name });
}
```
